{
  "title": "Deploying Batch Jobs using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide demonstrates how to create and deploy a simple batch job using the FastAPI framework along with Python 3.12+. The example provided includes a queue-based approach for handling multiple tasks concurrently.",

  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI is a modern, fast (high-performance), web framework for building APIs with Python 3.7+",
    "This guide uses Python 3.12+, which includes new features like pattern matching and improved performance.",
    "We'll create a batch job that can handle multiple tasks concurrently using a queue-based approach.",
    "The example includes setting up the FastAPI app, creating routes for task submission, and managing tasks in a Redis queue.",
    "You will need to have Redis installed and running on your system."
  ],

  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, BackgroundTasks\nimport redis\n\napp = FastAPI()\n\nredis_client = redis.Redis()\n\n@app.post('/task/')\ndef submit_task(background_tasks: BackgroundTasks):\n    task_id = str(redis_client.incr('task_id'))\n    redis_client.lpush('tasks', task_id)\n    background_tasks.add_task(process_task, task_id)\n```"
    },
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\n@app.background_task\ndef process_task(task_id):\n    task = redis_client.lpop('tasks')\n    # Process the task here (e.g., perform some computation)...\n    print(f'Processed task: {task}')\n```"
    }
  ],

  "version_notes": [
    "This guide is specific to FastAPI version 0.73.0 and Python 3.12. If you want to use a different version, adjust the code accordingly.",
    "Ensure your system has Redis installed and running before executing this example."
  ],

  "caveats": [
    "The provided FastAPI app only demonstrates a basic structure for handling batch jobs. For production-level deployments, additional considerations such as task prioritization, error handling, and scaling should be addressed.",
    "This guide does not cover the setup of Redis or database configurations. You can find more information about setting up Redis in its official documentation."
  ]
}
